o their total scores. Its mean squared error bound is\noptimized from $O(\\frac{d^5}{n\\epsilon^2})$ to $O(\\frac{d^4}{n\\epsilon^2})$,\nand its maximum magnitude risk bound is reduced to $O(\\frac{d^2}{n\\epsilon})$.\nExperimental results validate that our proposed approaches averagely reduce\nestimation error by $50\\%$ and are more robust to adversarial attacks.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 14 Aug 2019 01:53:48 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-08-15"}
