 neutrino\nenergies ($\\langle E_{\\nu} \\rangle \\sim 3.15~T$), with the softer equation of\nstate characterized by systematically larger decoupling temperatures ($\\Delta T\n\\lesssim 1~{\\rm MeV}$). Neutrinos streaming at infinity with different energies\ncome from very different regions of the remnant. The presence of a massive NS\nor of a BH in the remnant influences the neutrino thermalization process.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 14 Aug 2019 04:44:56 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 30 Sep 2020 13:41:02 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-10-01"}
