 the new main\naxis is an anti-correlation with black hole mass. In this case the secondary\naxis likely represents luminosity. However, given the results of previous\nstudies, inclination angle likely plays a role in H$\\beta{}$ width.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 14 Aug 2019 07:12:21 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 1 Oct 2019 08:12:31 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 15 Oct 2019 06:04:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-01-08"}
